 Johnny Depp and Amber Heard | Image: Sky News Johnny Depp and Amber Heard’s trial resumes today after an eleven-day break. Since the beginning of the trial, the court has been in session for a total of 15 days and has had the two giving their testimonies to the events that took place between them. Many witnesses have also taken the stand to give their testimonies that will be used to corroborate the claims made by Johnny Depp and Amber Heard. Johnny Depp sued his ex-wife Amber Heard for 50 million dollars after she defamed him in an article that labeled him an abuser, even though the Pirates of The Caribbean star’s name was not mentioned. In response, Amber Heard on a counter sue is asking for Depp for 100 million dollars.